<br>
I heard that furious bash is &quot;broken&quot; at the moment - but I dont know - I'm holding aggro through some pretty nasty nukes. Yes - for the first 10-15 seconds I seem to have less aggro than if I rushed in duel wielding BUT after that time I notice I don't lose aggro at all. <br>
<br>
I wonder how much regular bashing increases aggro? With the shield I am pretty confident that I can get higher on the aggro list than I can with a second procing weapon plus I get about 80 armor, 125 HP, and less ripostes.<br>
<br>
Granted - early in a fight I've had others steal aggro kind of fast (others being one warrior with an EB item and the other being another warrior duelling SOD's - both getting early procs) but after I build a little aggro I'm never touching the taunt key - last night in a 7 minute fight on one of the VT guys with the wizards raining in 5 and 6k crits there at the end (and when they usually are dumping mana and getting killed).<br>
<br>
Jury is still out and I admit I remain skeptical - but in a 30 person raid my second hand DPS over bash DPS isnt going to make or break us so I'm trying to experiment - I havent been disappointed. Other warriors with the sheild though - not as optimistic.<br>
<br>
Oh yea, naturally if I get a BOW Im going to bag this but that just might not happen. Might be all I get is an EB weapon and SOD/Shield.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
