<br>
The question is does bash work better than duel wield.<br>
<br>
Kind of easy to test if we do it like this.<br>
<br>
I have a SOD, primal weapons, and FB sheild.<br>
<br>
I can easily get another sheild.<br>
<br>
I can borrow a BOC from people.<br>
<br>
Head to Wakening Lands.<br>
<br>
Always have SOD in my main hand.<br>
<br>
Aggro the mist panther and have a shaman cast a definitive number of slows on the mob - a mist panther shouldnt be able to kill a shaman if we have a cleric on hand.<br>
<br>
Example - Shaman pulls mist panther and casts &quot;slow&quot; 5 times.<br>
<br>
Use five set-ups.<br>
<br>
1) Duel wield SOD + primal<br>
2) Duel wield SOD + BOC <br>
3) SOD + regular sheild<br>
4) SOD + FB shield<br>
5) 2HS primal<br>
<br>
Have the shaman cast slow at regular intervals - say 5 slows initially and then a slow every 30 seconds. Do that for 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
Look at the log for how long it took to get aggro, if the warrior lost aggro, how long it took to get aggro back.<br>
<br>
Of course if the warrior cant get aggro back with any of the combo's then the amount of slows will have to be adjusted - I guess we could do it with snare but slow is a nice aggro building and will prevent the shaman from dying - the mist panther is kind of a benchmark for warrior testing (AC and such).<br>
<br>
That's from my guild's board - I'll try and make that happen and post results.<br>
<br>
<br>
